$ SQL: boolean data type

According to the → misc/ISO/9075[SQL standared (ISO 9075)], the boolean data type is an optional
→ misc/ISO/9075/features[feature (with ID T031)].

The values that can be assigned to a boolean are
  • `true`
  • `false`
  • `null` or `unknown` (unless specified as `not null`)

